# Chrome Extension (MV3)

- Manifest V3 only: service worker background, no persistent background page.
- Cross-context communication uses `chrome.runtime.sendMessage`, `chrome.runtime.onMessage`, and long-lived `chrome.runtime.connect` ports — not shared memory or direct imports across contexts.
- Side panel binds via port name `autoapplyai-sidepanel`; background tracks `sidepanelPort` and tab binding.
- Content scripts: handle `chrome.runtime.lastError` on every async callback; never assume the tab has a listener.
- External dashboard talks to extension via `chrome.runtime.onMessageExternal` (see `externally_connectable` in manifest).
- Permissions/host_permissions changes require updating `public/manifest.json` and rebuilding.
